the ddp-client-java directory allows the java app to act as a client to the meteor server (it basically just takes all the code form src/ and just adapts it to run with meteor)

the infrastructure for communication was developed by advantageous on github but all the BRBT relevant code is found under java_applications/

COMPILE:
cd ddp-client-java
gradle jar

EXECUTE:
cd ddp-client-java
java -jar java_applications/world-subscription/build/libs/world-subscription.jar
